00:24:41,261 --> 00:24:42,749
my father's
testing Fizzle Rocks

488
00:24:42,841 --> 00:24:44,756
on the patients
at The Sisters of Quiet Mercy.

489
00:24:44,848 --> 00:24:47,839
Moreover, she saw
your Uncle Claudius with him,

490
00:24:47,931 --> 00:24:50,929
using Blossom Maple trucks
to deliver the drugs.

491
00:24:51,021 --> 00:24:52,649
Shades of
the Legion of Doom.

492
00:24:52,741 --> 00:24:54,676
They're planning
something big, Cheryl.

493
00:24:54,768 --> 00:24:56,676
My father likened it
to the apocalypse.

494
00:24:56,768 --> 00:24:58,209
For all we know,

495
00:24:58,301 --> 00:25:00,816
my father may somehow be
responsible for the seizures,

496
00:25:00,908 --> 00:25:03,579
but he wouldn't be
any more specific than that.

497
00:25:03,671 --> 00:25:05,856
So I was thinking maybe
we could ask your mom,

498
00:25:05,948 --> 00:25:07,486
since she's in cahoots
with him?

499
00:25:08,331 --> 00:25:10,159
With pleasure, Veronica.

500
00:25:10,251 --> 00:25:12,999
My Vixens have fallen.
My T.T. has fallen.

501
00:25:13,091 --> 00:25:16,826
If my gorgon-like mother has any knowledge
of how or why that's happening,

502
00:25:16,918 --> 00:25:18,216
we'll get it out of her.

503
00:25:26,271 --> 00:25:27,439
Hi, Sister. Sorry.

504
00:25:27,531 --> 00:25:29,336
I was wondering
if I could get some...

505
00:25:34,181 --> 00:25:36,456
Don't scream, Sister.

506
00:25:36,548 --> 00:25:37,689
Oh, sorry.

507
00:25:37,781 --> 00:25:39,826
You're coming with me.

508
00:25:40,901 --> 00:25:43,746
It's time we pay
a little visit to your King.

509
00:26:02,588 --> 00:26:04,766
It's just me. Get up.

510
00:26:06,311 --> 00:26:09,016
I didn't want to talk in front
of Archie and the others.

511
00:26:09,981 --> 00:26:11,719
As it turns out,

512
00:26:11,811 --> 00:26:14,086
Peabody had a lot to say.

513
00:26:14,178 --> 00:26:18,899
The bounty on your pal Archie,
it's not just on him.

514
00:26:18,991 --> 00:26:22,899
It's on anyone who's with him
or is helping him.

515
00:26:22,991 --> 00:26:26,689
Which means there is a target
on your back now, too, Jughead.

516
00:26:26,781 --> 00:26:28,676
It's the same if he goes
back to Riverdale.

517
00:26:28,768 --> 00:26:30,756
Archie's dad,
Archie's friends,

518
00:26:30,848 --> 00:26:32,529
everyone is at risk,

519
00:26:32,621 --> 00:26:34,106
which is why
you got to cut him loose.

520
00:26:34,198 --> 00:26:36,446
I'm not just gonna
ditch Archie, Mom.

521
00:26:36,538 --> 00:26:37,989
He's my best friend.

522
00:26:38,081 --> 00:26:39,676
Your mom's right, Jug.

523
00:26:42,681 --> 00:26:44,719
You got me this far.

524
00:26:44,811 --> 00:26:46,391
That's more than anyone else
would've done.

525
00:26:46,468 --> 00:26:47,709
You can go home.

526
00:26:47,801 --> 00:26:49,209
What are you talking about?

527
00:26:49,301 --> 00:26:50,586
You can't go
out there alone.

528
00:26:50,678 --> 00:26:52,889
Jug, Hiram almost killed us
back at that farm,

529
00:26:52,981 --> 00:26:54,626
Penny tracked us here
to your mom's.

530
00:26:54,718 --> 00:26:56,099
I've put her in danger.

531
00:26:56,191 --> 00:26:58,636
I've put Jellybean in danger.
I can't keep doing that.

532
00:26:59,561 --> 00:27:02,806
Wherever I go next,
it's got to be alone.

533
00:27:02,898 --> 00:27:04,326
- Archie.
- Jug.

534
00:27:12,801 --> 00:27:14,126
All right.

535
00:27:15,331 --> 00:27:17,049
So, it's decided.

536
00:27:17,141 --> 00:27:18,421
Arch, we'll get you
a ride to the border.

537
00:27:18,498 --> 00:27:19,781
I know a guy up there
who can help.

538
00:27:19,858 --> 00:27:22,716
Jughead, you can stay here
as long as you want.

539
00:27:25,891 --> 00:27:27,386
No, I think
I need to go home.

540
00:27:29,221 --> 00:27:30,976
Hiram Lodge needs
to get taken down.

541
00:27:32,151 --> 00:27:33,996
It's only gonna happen
from the inside.

542
00:27:37,071 --> 00:27:38,816
You sinful girls.

543
00:27:38,908 --> 00:27:43,116
I will strap you to your beds and
electroshock the sin out of you.

544
00:27:44,241 --> 00:27:48,769
Sister, monsters don't scare
me, and neither do you.

545
00:27:48,861 --> 00:27:51,606
I've seen real darkness. I've
stared it right in the face.

546
00:27:51,698 --> 00:27:53,569
That's why
you couldn't break me.

547
00:27:53,661 --> 00:27:55,356
I know the scam
that you're running.

548
00:27:55,448 --> 00:27:56,946
I saw you with Hiram Lodge.

549
00:27:57,038 --> 00:28:00,096
You're testing his drugs
out on patients.

550
00:28:00,188 --> 00:28:01,499
Why?

551
00:28:01,591 --> 00:28:04,409
Mr. Lodge is
a generous donor.

552
00:28:04,501 --> 00:28:06,579
- Oh?
- A believer in our mission.

553
00:28:06,671 --> 00:28:08,146
And by "mission", you mean

554
00:28:08,238 --> 00:28:12,056
using the game and the
Gargoyle King to scare girls?

555
00:28:12,531 --> 00:28:14,309
To torture children?

556
00:28:14,401 --> 00:28:17,629
The children who come
through our doors are broken.

557
00:28:17,721 --> 00:28:19,826
It's our sacred mission
to fix them,

558
00:28:19,918 --> 00:28:22,259
using whatever tools
necessary.

559
00:28:22,351 --> 00:28:25,906
Does that mean that the sisters
created Gryphons and Gargoyles

560
00:28:27,071 --> 00:28:28,171
as a tool?

561
00:28:31,211 --> 00:28:34,466
Misbehaving children have been
brought down to this room

562
00:28:34,558 --> 00:28:36,739
since the asylum opened.

563
00:28:36,831 --> 00:28:39,869
That statue scared them
into submission.

564
00:28:39,961 --> 00:28:42,566
Some of them,
the more disturbed ones,

565
00:28:42,658 --> 00:28:44,326
created a fantasy realm,

566
00:28:44,418 --> 00:28:45,969
a game

567
00:28:46,061 --> 00:28:48,596
to cope with the fear
of the one they'd named

568
00:28:49,471 --> 00:28:51,016
the Gargoyle King.

569
00:28:52,441 --> 00:28:55,266
We embraced it
as a therapeutic tool.

570
00:28:55,551 --> 00:28:56,889
And it worked

571
00:28:56,981 --> 00:29:00,326
because it embeds itself
in the minds of the players.

572
00:29:00,418 --> 00:29:03,139
It makes them complacent.
Focuses them.

573
00:29:03,231 --> 00:29:06,516
If that's true, then how did the
game get out into the world?

574
00:29:06,608 --> 00:29:08,046
Did you give it to Hiram?

575
00:29:08,138 --> 00:29:10,666
It was never meant
to leave these walls.

576
00:29:10,758 --> 00:29:12,376
It's too powerful.

577
00:29:12,468 --> 00:29:14,519
A game born of madness.

578
00:29:14,611 --> 00:29:17,169
A madness you helped nurture.

579
00:29:17,261 --> 00:29:19,386
And now people like
Ben and Dilton are dead.

580
00:29:19,478 --> 00:29:22,699
You're going to pay for everything
that you've done, Sister.

581
00:29:22,791 --> 00:29:24,706
And you're going
to tell the authorities

582
00:29:24,798 --> 00:29:26,846
what you've told us
about the game.

583
00:29:27,631 --> 00:29:29,766
And about Hiram's donations.

584
00:29:31,461 --> 00:29:35,589
I only answer
to one authority, Betty.

585
00:29:35,681 --> 00:29:38,196
Come on, Ethel.
We have her keys.

586
00:29:38,288 --> 00:29:39,839
We're leaving.

587
00:29:39,931 --> 00:29:42,379
We're taking your children
with us, Sister.

588
00:29:42,471 --> 00:29:43,796
They won't want to leave.

589
00:29:44,621 --> 00:29:46,316
We'll see about that.

590
00:29:50,611 --> 00:29:51,716
Help!

591
00:29:51,808 --> 00:29:53,039
Help!

592
00:29:53,131 --> 00:29:55,496
I'm in the basement.

593
00:29:56,211 --> 00:29:57,211
Help!

594
00:29:59,858 --> 00:30:02,209
Let's do this again.

595
00:30:02,301 --> 00:30:05,219
What does my father
have planned for Riverdale?

596
00:30:05,311 --> 00:30:07,356
Speak!
Or it gets the syrup again.

597
00:30:09,078 --> 00:30:13,369
Why do you want to know
your father's plans?

598
00:30:13,461 --> 00:30:17,816
He's finally going to turn this
backwater into something worthwhile.

599
00:30:17,908 --> 00:30:20,639
A place where
we can all pursue

600
00:30:20,731 --> 00:30:25,069
- our various enterprises unmolested.
- What does that mean?

601
00:30:25,161 --> 00:30:28,456
She's talking about
drug dealing and prostitution.

602
00:30:28,548 --> 00:30:30,656
Aren't you, you ghoulunatic?

603
00:30:37,991 --> 00:30:39,496
We need specifics.

604
00:30:40,751 --> 00:30:44,616
How exactly is my father
planning on turning Riverdale

605
00:30:44,708 --> 00:30:45,936
into Vice City?

606
00:30:46,028 --> 00:30:49,499
Well, he's in bed
with the mayor, isn't he?

607
00:30:49,591 --> 00:30:51,976
And as for
law enforcement, well,

608
00:30:52,068 --> 00:30:54,339
the last time I checked,

609
00:30:54,431 --> 00:30:56,636
Riverdale didn't have
much of a sheriff.

610
00:30:58,531 --> 00:31:01,249
Details. Or so help me God,

611
00:31:01,341 --> 00:31:03,629
I will drown you
in this cheap crap.

612
00:31:03,721 --> 00:31:05,986
And open the garden doors
to let the ants in.

613
00:31:07,741 --> 00:31:10,819
All right, I'll tell you.

614
00:31:10,911 --> 00:31:13,556
Wait. What do you mean,
you don't want to escape?

615
00:31:13,648 --> 00:31:14,886
We feel safe here.

616
00:31:14,978 --> 00:31:16,269
We play G&G.

617
00:31:16,361 --> 00:31:19,769
The sisters give us candy,
keep us warm and clean.

618
00:31:19,861 --> 00:31:21,456
Why would we
wanna leave?

619
00:31:25,581 --> 00:31:26,986
Sister Woodhouse was right.

620
00:31:27,078 --> 00:31:29,156
They're all brainwashed,
just like I was.

621
00:31:29,248 --> 00:31:31,379
Well, we can't just
leave them behind.

622
00:31:31,471 --> 00:31:34,646
Not to mention all those kids in the
gay conversion wing where Cheryl was.

623
00:31:34,738 --> 00:31:37,596
There has to be
something we can do.

624
00:31:38,811 --> 00:31:41,049
Wait, the game.

625
00:31:41,141 --> 00:31:44,509
The game is how they cope
with terror, right?

626
00:31:44,601 --> 00:31:47,986
So, let's convince them to escape
by turning it into a quest.

627
00:31:48,821 --> 00:31:51,536
The Gargoyle King
inspires fear,

628
00:31:51,628 --> 00:31:53,729
so let's give them hope.

629
00:31:53,821 --> 00:31:56,546
Let's give them the opposite of
the Gargoyle King, which is...

630
00:31:56,638 --> 00:31:57,936
The Gryphon Queen.

631
00:32:06,911 --> 00:32:08,529
All right.

632
00:32:08,621 --> 00:32:11,516
Now, I packed you guys
some lunches for the road.

633
00:32:13,181 --> 00:32:16,056
Hey, Jug, you mind getting that?
It's probably Archie's ride.

634
00:32:24,811 --> 00:32:25,861
Dad!

635
00:32:27,721 --> 00:32:29,426
I've missed you
so much, Dad.

636
00:32:29,518 --> 00:32:31,236
Me too, son.

637
00:32:43,211 --> 00:32:45,129
So you finally made it, huh?

638
00:32:45,221 --> 00:32:47,666
Jughead's getting his bag.
He'll be out in a minute.

639
00:32:48,791 --> 00:32:50,126
Hey, Jellybelly.

640
00:32:51,141 --> 00:32:52,676
You've gotten so big.

641
00:32:54,721 --> 00:32:56,046
Can I get a hug?

642
00:32:56,311 --> 00:32:57,326
Can I get a dad?

643
00:32:57,418 --> 00:32:58,691
Hey, JB!

644
00:32:59,311 --> 00:33:00,369
Come on now.

645
00:33:00,461 --> 00:33:02,096
Let her be. I deserve that.

646
00:33:03,231 --> 00:33:04,839
She misses you.

647
00:33:04,931 --> 00:33:07,256
She'd just rather fight
than admit it.

648
00:33:07,348 --> 00:33:09,336
Yeah, like mother
like daughter.

649
00:33:09,428 --> 00:33:10,979
Dad.

650
00:33:11,071 --> 00:33:12,696
I see Mom called you.

651
00:33:14,241 --> 00:33:16,066
Thought you might be
missing this.

652
00:33:20,501 --> 00:33:23,126
I heard Penny was here
causing trouble.

653
00:33:23,218 --> 00:33:25,239
No problem at all.

654
00:33:25,331 --> 00:33:28,126
I don't think we have to worry
much about Penny anymore.

655
00:33:32,421 --> 00:33:33,836
Come here, kid.

656
00:33:35,211 --> 00:33:36,536
I'm gonna miss you.

657
00:33:40,261 --> 00:33:43,136
Go warm up the bikes,
will you, Jug?

658
00:33:45,731 --> 00:33:47,686
Thank you, Gladys,
for the call.

659
00:33:48,441 --> 00:33:50,046
I'll make sure
he gets home safe.

660
00:33:59,281 --> 00:34:00,736
Get out of here.

661
00:34:06,291 --> 00:34:07,826
<i>Kevin, cadets!</i>

662
00:34:09,961 --> 00:34:11,699
This meal's on the house.

663
00:34:11,791 --> 00:34:13,436
But you brutes
are helping us out.

664
00:34:13,528 --> 00:34:15,516
We need backup
right the hell now.

665
00:34:15,608 --> 00:34:16,926
What's going on?

666
00:34:19,251 --> 00:34:20,886
On your feet, soldier boys!

667
00:34:21,381 --> 00:34:23,039
We're going to war.

668
00:34:23,131 --> 00:34:24,766
Paladins and Hellcasters,

669
00:34:25,721 --> 00:34:27,026
Healers and Deadeyes,

670
00:34:27,118 --> 00:34:30,036
your Game Master has
a new adventure for you.

671
00:34:30,128 --> 00:34:33,339
Your goal is to escape

672
00:34:33,431 --> 00:34:35,196
from the Gargoyle King's
fortress.

673
00:34:37,321 --> 00:34:40,256
But we can't. If he catches
us, we'll be punished.

674
00:34:40,348 --> 00:34:42,639
Yes. Severely.

675
00:34:42,731 --> 00:34:43,816
But there is hope.

676
00:34:43,908 --> 00:34:46,186
A Queen to lead you
into the light.

677
00:34:46,278 --> 00:34:48,286
Hark, there she be!

678
00:34:59,351 --> 00:35:03,589
Follow me,
your Gryphon Queen,

679
00:35:03,681 --> 00:35:07,206
away from this fortress, and back
to the kingdom of Eldervair!

680
00:35:07,298 --> 00:35:08,766
But what about the King?

681
00:35:13,511 --> 00:35:15,936
The King is dead.

682
00:35:16,531 --> 00:35:18,526
You're all free.

683
00:35:22,361 --> 00:35:24,506
We can't wake
the King's Demon Soldiers.

684
00:35:24,598 --> 00:35:26,106
I have the enchanted keys.

685
00:35:26,198 --> 00:35:28,746
Meet me at
the doors to freedom.

686
00:36:12,341 --> 00:36:14,609
Here you go.

687
00:36:14,701 --> 00:36:17,356
It's the last stop
before the border.

688
00:36:17,448 --> 00:36:18,859
Yeah.

689
00:36:18,951 --> 00:36:21,369
You know, I was thinking.
I could go with you.

690
00:36:21,461 --> 00:36:22,829
We could do this together.

691
00:36:22,921 --> 00:36:24,286
Find a cabin in the woods?

692
00:36:24,378 --> 00:36:27,236
Yeah. Teach you carpentry,
like my old man did me.

693
00:36:27,328 --> 00:36:28,636
Imagine that.

694
00:36:29,011 --> 00:36:30,769
Us.

695
00:36:30,861 --> 00:36:32,776
Living off the land,
father and son.

696
00:36:32,868 --> 00:36:34,799
Hunting, fishing.

697
00:36:34,891 --> 00:36:36,459
It would be great.

698
00:36:36,551 --> 00:36:38,066
Yeah, it would be.

699
00:36:39,941 --> 00:36:43,446
But, uh, you know
we can't do that.

700
00:36:43,701 --> 00:36:45,236
Right, Dad?

701
00:36:47,401 --> 00:36:48,946
I can't change your mind,

702
00:36:49,451 --> 00:36:50,816
get you to come back home?

703
00:36:56,161 --> 00:36:57,916
But you can
give me your blessing.

704
00:37:01,961 --> 00:37:03,686
I was your age
when my father passed away.

705
00:37:03,778 --> 00:37:06,676
- I never got to say goodbye...
- This isn't goodbye, Dad.

706
00:37:08,971 --> 00:37:10,766
You're damn right, it's not.

707
00:37:15,481 --> 00:37:16,986
See you soon?

708
00:37:17,078 --> 00:37:18,936
Yeah, you will.

709
00:37:19,911 --> 00:37:22,106
Oh, one more thing.

710
00:37:28,821 --> 00:37:30,286
Vegas!

711
00:37:58,591 --> 00:38:01,066
- Mom, stop!
- You heard the woman! Halt!

712
00:38:03,661 --> 00:38:05,199
Veronica, what is this?

713
00:38:05,291 --> 00:38:06,386
Consider it a coup d'moi.

714
00:38:06,478 --> 00:38:08,099
We know your end game.

715
00:38:08,191 --> 00:38:10,529
You are hereby relieved
of your mayoral duties.

716
00:38:10,621 --> 00:38:12,306
Those plans
you and your husband had

717
00:38:12,398 --> 00:38:13,726
with my dollymop mother

718
00:38:13,818 --> 00:38:15,979
are now canceled.

719
00:38:16,071 --> 00:38:18,379
Now, step away from the phone

720
00:38:18,471 --> 00:38:21,706
before you make the biggest
mistake of your life.

721
00:38:23,041 --> 00:38:24,466
Veronica...

722
00:38:25,551 --> 00:38:27,836
You can't just walk in here
and depose me.

723
00:38:28,291 --> 00:38:29,926
I'm an elected official.

724
00:38:32,301 --> 00:38:35,476
Besides, you're too late.

725
00:38:37,061 --> 00:38:39,339
The order went out
ten minutes ago.

726
00:38:39,431 --> 00:38:41,336
I was about
to call and tell you.

727
00:38:51,571 --> 00:38:52,896
It's starting.

728
00:38:58,321 --> 00:39:00,636
Betty, what are we going to do
with all these kids?

729
00:39:00,728 --> 00:39:02,159
They have nowhere to go.

730
00:39:02,251 --> 00:39:04,376
We'll help them, Ethel,
all of them.

731
00:39:07,501 --> 00:39:09,086
- Mom?
- Betty.

732
00:39:10,761 --> 00:39:13,079
Why are you wearing that outfit?
What's going on?

733
00:39:13,171 --> 00:39:15,456
- What are you doing here?
- Hell is breaking loose.

734
00:39:15,548 --> 00:39:17,866
I came to get you
out of the sisters'.

735
00:39:17,958 --> 00:39:21,936
Well, you're just in time,
but it's not just gonna be me.

736
00:39:26,061 --> 00:39:29,349
<i> And just like that,</i>
<i>in a few frantic moments,</i>

737
00:39:29,441 --> 00:39:30,956
<i>the town we'd known
all our lives</i>

738
00:39:31,048 --> 00:39:33,296
<i>was once again changed,</i>

739
00:39:33,388 --> 00:39:36,599
<i>but this time, irrevocably.</i>

740
00:39:36,691 --> 00:39:41,109
<i>It was time for us to brace
for a terrible impact.</i>

741
00:39:41,201 --> 00:39:44,896
<i>And while Archie Andrews headed away
from the doomed town of Riverdale,</i>

742
00:39:44,988 --> 00:39:47,039
<i>we raced towards it.</i>

743
00:39:47,131 --> 00:39:49,326
<i>For that night was
the fruition of a game</i>

744
00:39:49,418 --> 00:39:51,566
<i>that had been
planned for and played</i>

745
00:39:51,658 --> 00:39:53,716
<i>across the years.</i>

746
00:40:01,811 --> 00:40:02,949
The hell is this?

747
